<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I ran into this when trying to interoperate with a python XMLRPC server.</p>

<p>There is an extension to the xml spec which allows a  element in place of other values:
<a href="http://ontosys.com/xml-rpc/extensions.php">http://ontosys.com/xml-rpc/extensions.php</a></p>

<p>I have already implemented this building off of handling for booleans, but I would like feedback as to whether I should submit the changes back into the main codebase.</p>

<p>Are there any cases where someone is sending or recieving PHP NULL values and is counting on them to be translated differently, e.g. as FALSE?</p>

